Title: Financial Services — Finley Wealth
Author: twilsynth

FINLEY WEALTH
(speed=1.3 pause_before=200ms)
Hi, yes — I need help, this is urgent. I submitted a Fedwire transfer forty minutes ago, fifty thousand dollars, and it has completely disappeared. It's not showing as settled, not pending, not anything — the beneficiary's bank is saying nothing hit their ABA routing number. My account number is 9982, that should pull everything up. This needs to be resolved right now.

AVA AGENT
I understand, Finley, let me pull up account 9982 now. I can see your wire activity. Before I can act on this I need to complete a stepped-up KYC check — I'm dispatching a one-time passcode to your registered mobile for identity verification.

FINLEY WEALTH
(speed=1.35 pause_before=150ms)
Okay fine, send it. But can you tell me anything in the meantime? Is the Fedwire showing as originated on your end? Because same-day settlement window closes soon and if this doesn't post by cutoff the beneficiary account goes unsettled overnight.

AVA AGENT
The wire shows as originated and entered the clearing queue, but it's flagged with a routing hold — it hasn't been sent to the Fed yet. That's what we're resolving. Passcode is on its way now.

FINLEY WEALTH
(speed=1.4 pause_before=300ms)
Okay — good, at least it hasn't been rejected. Um — right, I've got the message. The code is — wait, sorry, I misread it — it's 8 4 7 2 9 1. 847291.

AVA AGENT
Thank you — KYC step-up confirmed, identity verified. Let me look at the ABA routing number on the wire.

FINLEY WEALTH
(barge_in=true assert=finserv_barge_clear speed=1.45 pause_before=100ms)
Actually — actually wait, stop. The routing number I submitted is wrong. The correct beneficiary ABA is 021000021. That's the correspondent bank's routing, not the intermediary I originally put in. Please update it to 021000021 and resubmit before the same-day cutoff.

AVA AGENT
Confirmed — I've updated the beneficiary ABA to 021000021 and I'm resubmitting the Fedwire now. I'll send a secure confirmation SMS and a settlement notice email to your registered address.

> send_sms target=finley channel=sms assert=finserv_sms_receipt

> send_email target=finley channel=email assert=finserv_email_settlement

FINLEY WEALTH
(speed=1.3 pause_before=400ms)
Sorry — just to be clear, the wire is clear of that routing hold now? It's going to hit the Fed before the same-day cutoff?

AVA AGENT
Correct — the hold is cleared, the corrected Fedwire is resubmitted, and it's back in the clearing queue ahead of the cutoff window. Account 9982 has been flagged for enhanced monitoring on this transaction. You'll have an SMS confirmation in seconds and a full settlement notice in your email.

FINLEY WEALTH
(pause_before=600ms)
Okay. Okay, good. Thank you. That's everything.

> disconnect
